                            </summary>

                            <p>If you have been raped or sexually assaulted and chose to go to the police, there are a few different options available for you to report it.

                            </p>

                            <u>Call <b>999</b> if there is still an immediate danger </u>
                            <br><br>
                            <p><b>Report online </b>


                                The met website gives the option to report online rather than speaking to an officer by telephone in the first instance, this is done securely and confidentially <a href="https://www.met.police.uk/ro/report/ocr/af/how-to-report-a-crime/">Report a crime</a>



                                All reports made using this service are reviewed by a 24/7 contact centre within a few hours and an officer will get back to you in a maximum of two days (although usually quicker). </p>
